      "role": "user",
      "content": "small goals feel like just playing house while the house is on fire. honestly, it feels more like we're all just pretending things matter. if the math is already decided and the planet is basically gone, what is the point of even sticking around to see it happen? it feels like everyone is just wasting time by trying to stay optimistic.",
